Introduction
============
MIT License
-----------

The Brill Framework (Client, Middleware and Server) is distributed under the MIT License, a copy of which 
is below. All source code modules covered by the MIT license contain the following first line:

// © 2023 Brill Software Limited - Brill Framework, distributed under the MIT license.

The MIT license is a permissive license, meaning it carries very few restrictions 
and basically allows you to do whatever you want with the code.

Your modifications
------------------

You can make modification to the Brill Framework modules and mark the changes with your own choice
of license. For example:

// Original: © 2023 Brill Software Limited - Brill Framework, distributed under the MIT license.
// Modifications: // © 2023 Traders Inc. - Trading App, distributed under the Traders Inc. license.

You don't need to identify the exact lines of code that were changed, as these can be found using Git.

It would be appreciated if you were able to make any generally applicable changes and fixes under the MIT 
license, so that they could be included into future releases of the Brill Framework.

Your Applications and Components
--------------------------------

Any applications developed by you using the Brill Framework are by default 
your copyright with "all rights reserved". To change this, place a copyright
notice on the first line of each module and specify the license. For example:

// © 2023 Traders Inc. - Trading App, distributed under the Traders Inc. License.

You can sell any applications and components you develop, using your choice of license. 
Make sure to read and follow the license terms of any third party components you use.

