TERMS AND CONDITIONS

0. Definitions.

"The License" refers to version 1.0 of the Brill Software Apps License.

"App" refers to the pages, database scripts, resource files and React 
components that comprise an application and are the copyrightable work licensed 
under this License.

"source code" refers to the Typescript component code and JavaScript code.

"You" refers to the Licensee. The licensee could be a person or an orgransiation.

"personal use" refers to usage by, only and only, the licensee, and not by any 
other person or organisation related in any way to the licensee.

1. Usage

You are free to download, copy, compile, study and refer to the source code, pages, 
database scripts and other resource files for an evaluation period of 30 days.

After the 30 day evaluation period, if you wish to continue to use the App, you need
to purchase a license. See the Brill Software Pricing page for more details.

Usage by you of any work covered by this license should not, directly or indirectly, 
enable its usage by any other individual or organisation.

2. Modifications

You are free to make any modifications to the source code, pages, database scripts 
and other resource files covered by this license. You are also free to compile the 
source after modifying it and using the complied product obtain thereafter in 
compliance with this License. You may provide such modifications back to Brill 
Software, as you see fit, but there is no obligation on the part of Brill Software 
to include such modifications into future releases.

3. Redistribution

You may redistribute the Brill Framework, including your own applications, but not 
with the Brill Software Apps included. The Brill Software Apps are to be deleted 
by removing the app top level directory and its contents. You may also want to 
delete the App specific components, but this is at your discretion.

If you wish to redistribute any Brill Software Apps, please contact Brill Software 
to obtain permission.

4. Non-compliance

You may not copy, modify, sublicense, or distribute the Brill Software Apps except 
as expressly provided under this License. Any attempt otherwise to copy, modify,
sublicense or distribute the Brill Software Apps is void, and will automatically
terminate your rights under this License.

5. Acceptance of License

You are not required to accept this License, since you have not signed it. However, 
nothing else grants you permission to modify or use the source. These actions are
prohibited by law if you do not accept this License. Therefore, by modifying or 
using the source ( or any work based on the source), you indicate your acceptance
of this License to do so, and all its terms and conditions for copying, 
redistributing or modifying the source or works based on it.

6. Permissions

If you intend to incorporate the source code, pages, database scripts and resource files in 
part or whole, into any free or proprietary distribution, you need to explicitly write to the 
Brill Software to ask for permission.

7. No Warranty

The source code licensed under this license is shared "as is". Since it is intended for 
